data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
Loki - It allowes You to baypass JellyBean bootloader - You can't use it, when You currently have KitKat or Lollipop bootloader, unless You'll get bootloader error.
BUMP - You can use it on JellyBean, KitKat and also on Lollipop bootstack.

data.name: textBox4.Text
data.value:
You should use this option when it is needed. Generally in almost threads on XDA is written which bootloader You should have.
LP Original - Only for stock ROM (custom kernels and recoveries will've been killed). LP Bump - required in most ROMs built on LG's Lollipop. LP Loki - required in almost AOSP Lollipop and Marshmallows.
KitKat and JellyBean bootloaders are old and rarely used, so use it when You flash old ROM.
